Dr. Christina Paxson is the president of Brown University.

‚ÄúAnd Hunter, thank you very much too,‚Äù Li continued. ‚ÄúAll the best to you all.‚Äù

A New York City mother who asked Mayor Eric Adams why he reneged on his promise to "unmask our toddlers" was fired shortly after putting Adams on blast.



According to the NY Post, Daniela Jampel - who was an assistant corporation counsel in the city Law Department, learned she was fired 'less than an hour' after confronting the Mayor at an unrelated LGBTQ event which had a podium banner reading "Come to the city where you can say whatever you want."


"Three weeks ago, you told parents to trust you that you would unmask our toddlers," said Jampel. "You stood right here, and you said that the masks would come off April 4. That has not happened."

When City Hall staffers attempted to cut Jampel off, Adams told them to let her speak - only to condescend to her by telling her she needed to "come to a conclusion."

GREAT FALLS PACHYDERM CLUB
LIBERTY HALL    721 10TH AVE SOUTH
THURSDAYS NOON TO 1:00 PM


This Thursday, our guest speakers will be former State Senator, Ed Butcher, and James Bergstrom, candidate for HD 30, which runs along the eastern side of Cascade County.  
Find out more about James Bergstrom here:
https://bergstrom4hd30.com/

Upcoming speakers*
The following programs are scheduled for the Great Falls Pachyderm Club:

    April 14 - Desma Meissner, candidate for SD12 and Mark Finnicum, School Board member and candidate

    April 21 - Jay  Groskreutz, candidate for Sheriff

    April 28 - Jesse Slaughter, candidate for Sheriff

    May 5 - Christie Slaughter, Corrections Specialist

    May 12 - Shane Etzwiler, Great Falls Chamber of Commerce and John Faulkner, Great Falls International Airport Director

    May 19 - Eric Bailey, Justice of the Peace candidate

    May 26 - Jim Brown, MT Supreme Court Candidate
* schedule subject to change without notice

We will be serving hamburgers and hotdogs for lunch, along with chips and a beverage.

ALLIANCE FOR YOUTH BUILDING -
